I want to help people.  I want to work with children. I want to help families. I want to be a social worker. I see a job with the Division of Family and Children Services.

I think good social workers care about people. They treat people with respect. They do what is right. They want to help people get along. They want to learn new things. 

I have always wanted to help people. I saw people with problems. Some people did not want to see their problems. Some people tried to hide their problems. I saw this in high school and college. I got a degree in Psychology. 

I met a boy one day. He was sixteen. He was scared. He was at a friend's house. He had left his parents. His parents were mean to him. I talked to the police. I told them I was a psychologist. The police asked me to talk to his parents. I talked to the parents. They did not like that he called the police. They said he was lying.  This made me think about being a social worker. 

Social workers help people who are treated unfairly.

Society says everyone is important. But sometimes people are not treated fairly. I do not like this.  I want to fight for what is right. I did this in high school and college. I wore different clothes. I colored my hair. I joined groups. I fought against racism. I fought against meanness. I will continue to fight for what is right.

This paper talks about sleep problems. There are two ways to look at them:

* **The body:** This way looks at genes and how the body works.

* **The world around us:** This way looks at how things like family, friends, and money affect sleep.

This paper looks at studies about sleep problems and how they fit with these two ways of thinking. It also talks about the good and bad parts of each study.

Sleep problems can be many things. Some are caused by things like feeling sad or anxious. Others are caused by things like breathing problems or taking medicine.

Some common sleep problems include:

* **Trouble falling asleep or staying asleep:** This is called insomnia.
* **Sleeping too much:** This is called hypersomnia.
* **Falling asleep suddenly:** This is called narcolepsy.

The body way of looking at sleep problems says that our genes and how our bodies work can cause problems. For example, some people have a special part in their brain that helps them sleep. If this part does not work right, it can cause sleep problems.

The world around us way of looking at sleep problems says that things like stress, work, and family can cause problems. For example, if someone is worried about work, they may have trouble sleeping.

This paper looks at a study about a part in the brain that helps people sleep. The study found that this part is important for sleep. If it does not work right, it can cause sleep problems. This study shows that our genes and our bodies can both cause sleep problems.

This paper talk about three things about Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD). First, it say what CAPD is. Next, it talk about how to see if someone has CAPD. Last, it talk about how a teacher can help a student with CAPD in a regular classroom.

CAPD, or Auditory Processing Disorder (APD), is when the brain have trouble using sound. A person with CAPD can hear sounds. But, the part of the brain that makes sense of sound does not work well. It has trouble with things like understanding words and hearing sounds in different places.

People first talk about CAPD in the 1950s. At that time, they called it "auditory imperception."

CAPD can show up in many ways. A person with CAPD may not hear sounds well if they are in different places. They may have trouble telling sounds apart. They may have trouble understanding sounds that follow patterns. They may not understand jokes or sarcasm. One sound may cover up another sound. They may have trouble understanding sounds all together.

To see if someone has CAPD, a doctor will watch how they listen and give them tests. They may use tests with words and numbers. They may measure the sounds in the ear. There is no one test that can always tell if someone has CAPD.

Twelfth Night show that disguise can help people hide. But it can also cause problems. People must decide if they want to keep hiding or be honest. If they tell the truth, others may be mad.

Disguise can be hard when it involves gender. Why do people pretend to be the opposite gender? In Twelfth Night, Viola hides to be safe. She says, "I'll bring you to a captain in this town/ Where lie my maiden weeds, by whose gentle help/ I was preserved to serve this noble count…"

Viola's plan works, but she feels alone. She can't be with other women. Olivia, a woman, thinks Viola is a man. She says, "Whither, my lord? Cesario, husband, stay.”  Viola also feels love for Orsino, a man.

Twelfth Night shows how hiding can make people feel strong emotions. Olivia and Orsino may like Viola because she is pretending to be a man.  

Olivia loves Cesario, then loves Sebastian, who looks like Viola. This shows Olivia may not judge people well.

Viola says, "A sister, you are she.”  This shows Viola and Olivia are now close friends.

German rule in Africa was bad. It was very bad for the Ovaherero and Nama people. Many people died.  

But not all of German rule was the same.  Some places were better than others. German East Africa was good.  The British took over in 1919 and found many Africans who could read and write.

But in South West Africa, things were different. The German government did not help educate the African people there.  They asked churches to teach the children. 

The Germans did help European children learn. They built schools and gave money to churches. This made a big difference for South West Africa. Even after Germany left, most Africans there could not read or write. 

This paper will look at why South West Africa was so different. We will look at the people who lived there and how the government treated them.


There are many books about German schools in Africa. Most are in German. They are old, from when Germany ruled Africa.  Some people wrote books in English later. They compared schools in different places. They found big differences.

One book is about schools in South West Africa and East Africa. This book says that South West Africa had many European settlers. This is why the schools were different.

South West Africa was a good place to live. It was not too hot or too cold. Many Europeans moved there. By 1913, there were 15,000 Europeans there. East Africa had only 5,000.

Popular music has many types. There are so many, it is hard to list them all. Many types have small types, too. Heavy metal music is one type. It is a popular type. It is 40 years old.

Heavy metal music is different. It shows many feelings. The feelings are often sad or dark. Heavy metal music is also different because many small types have come from it.

Now there are so many small types of heavy metal. It is hard to say what heavy metal is. It has taken things from other types of music. But it started somewhere.

To understand heavy metal, we need to know what it is. It is a movement, not just a type. Heavy metal is strong music. It has loud drums, loud guitars, and loud voices.

Heavy metal music can be scary. It is often about dark things. Some people use drugs when they make this music. In the 1970s, people used drugs a lot. This made the music different.

Heavy metal music is different from other music. It does not talk about happy things. It talks about dark things. Some people like this music because it shows strong feelings.

Henri Rousseau was a painter. He made dreamlike art before the Surrealist artists. His painting, The Dream, show a woman in a dream. It also show Rousseau’s dreams. He wanted people to like his art. He wanted to be famous.

Rousseau did not learn to paint in school. He worked for the government for many years. He had a hard life. He lost his wife and many children. He started to paint when he was old. He wanted to be accepted by other artists. He wanted to be like them.

But Rousseau was different. He painted in his own way. He did not want to copy other artists. This made it hard for him to be famous. He was not like Matisse. Matisse was famous too. But Matisse painted in a different way.

Rousseau’s painting, The Dream, show his struggles. He wanted to be good enough for the art world. But he also wanted to be himself.

Many people think that good morals and good art are connected. I think this is true. A famous writer named John Keats said, "Beauty is truth, truth beauty- That is all / Ye know on earth, and all ye need to know.” We learn many things from school and life. But we know good morals and good art without being taught. Both good morals and good art try to explain things, not tell us what to do.

We study art and morals to understand why something is good or beautiful. We try to explain why a painting is good, or why an action is right. But we can never fully explain why something is good or beautiful.

For example, we can talk about a painting like the Mona Lisa. We can talk about colors and shapes. But these things do not tell us why it is good art. When someone likes a painting, they often say, “There’s just something about it.”  This shows that there is more to art than we can describe.

The same is true for morals. We can talk about right and wrong. But we can never fully explain why something is right or wrong.  A writer named Flannery O'Connor said, “A story is a way to say something that can’t be said any other way.”  Art and morals are like this. They have a special quality that we can’t fully understand.

I think this special quality is why art and morals are connected. We feel them deep inside. Art and morals are both important to us because they help us understand the world.

Germany is a strong country. It has many cultures. The cultures are all over Germany. From the mountains in München to the sea in Kiel. You can see the culture in Köln on the Rhine River. You can also see it in Dresden on the Elbe River. Many different groups of people made Germany. 

The land where the Germans live is called Germania.  

People do not know for sure where the name comes from. One writer, Tacitus, said the name came from a group of Germans called the Tungrians. They lived near the Rhine River. They fought with the Gauls.  Julius Caesar was another writer. He wrote about fighting the Gauls. He used the word “Germanus” to talk about the groups near the Rhine. He used it to show the difference between the Gauls and the Germans.

Some people think the name comes from a spear the Germans used. It was called a ger. Others think it comes from an old word that means “to shout.” The word is garim. 

Tacitus wrote about the Germans. He said they did not mix with other people. He said they were from the land. They did not come from other places.

The Romans fought with the Germans. They wanted things from them. They also fought in battles. But, the Romans did not stay in Germany.

I look down.  My mind is empty. I see the thing in front of me. I look at it. My mind tells me about it. But I do not feel. 
A long time ago, an artist told me to get a book. The book is called "The New Drawing on the Right Side of the Brain." I want to draw. I liked to draw when I was small. The book says how to draw. 

The book says to use a box. Put the box around the thing you want to draw. The box makes the thing smaller.  

I look at the thing in front of me. I want to use the box. But I can't. I am afraid. 

Good artists like Picasso and Monet. They made good art. I want to make good art, too.

I touch the thing. It is hard. I move my hand. I want to draw. The water is clear.  

The thing does not move. I push it again.  

I have a mop. I have a tie. I am unhappy. 

I look at the thing. It is bad. Someone put it there for me to clean. 

I clean the thing.

Teenagers have many problems when they drive. Many die in car accidents. This is bad news. The brains of teenagers are not ready to drive. They do not have enough experience.  Teen drivers have more accidents. They drive too fast. They drive off the road. 

Teenagers also have more accidents when friends are in the car. This is true. Many teens drive with friends.  A group in California looked at accidents. They saw that the more friends in the car, the more accidents.

Some states have rules for teen drivers. New drivers have limited time to drive. They can not have other teens in the car. These rules are good, but not enough.

The real problem is that teens are not ready to drive. They take risks. They like to go fast. A doctor said teens take risks until they are older. It is better to wait to get a driver’s license.

Teenagers will get licenses soon.  Many will drive. We need to make new rules to keep teens safe. Schools can teach them about driving. But no one under eighteen should drive. Teens need a special permit before they get a license. They need to practice with an adult.

The rules should be the same for all states. This will help keep teens safe everywhere.

New rules will help. We can save lives.

I look at old movies from the Library of Congress. I see many new tricks. These tricks use special cuts in the movie to make things look different. 

I want to know how these tricks work. I look at many movies. Most movies use simple tricks. They use the same parts of the movie set. The camera does not move. The movie is like a play on a stage. 

Many movies use long shots. The camera does not zoom in close to people. This is like a play too. The audience sees the whole stage.

Most tricks are short. They last about one minute. The tricks are like jokes or small magic acts.  

Sometimes one movie trick is made of many parts.  The parts are joined together. This makes the trick look good. Look at a movie called “The Execution of Mary, Queen of Scots.” It looks like one shot, but it is made of many parts.

John Taylor from Caroline like Republican ideas. He was a farmer.  His job and short time in politics made him known for talking about freedom. He liked the idea of farming. Most of his ideas about the government came from this. He wanted to help farmers. This made him talk about the government a lot. 

John Taylor thought the United States had a good chance to make a perfect system. There were no old ways to stop them. This meant they could make a system where people ruled themselves. He believed people had rights. He said if one right is taken away, they all are in danger. These rights should be safe from the government.  He said that in nature, strong people did well. But in a society, things should be different.

To make a good society, Taylor said the government should be good and bad. Taylor was very sure about good and bad. He said, “The government is run by people, so it will have good and bad parts” (page 167). He said good rules protect private things, help farming, and do not help big businesses. He said a good government works well, even if the people in charge are greedy.

Taylor said people are always thinking about themselves. He said this is bad only when it hurts others. A good government can keep people from doing bad things.

Taylor, like other Republicans, wanted the rules to be followed exactly. He wanted a small government. He did not want it to have more power than the rules said. He knew a big government costs a lot of money and could be mean. He also said that just following the rules without thinking can be bad. He thought the Declaration of Independence was more important than the Constitution because it said the United States was a group of states, not one country.

Figure 17 show a big drop in log write in the third month. This was sad. We do not know why.

Winter come to the New England school. People ride bike or walk less. This may be one reason for the drop.

December is the end of the school year. Students are very busy. They may forget to write in the log. 

December is also the holiday time. Students and teachers have a long break. They do not come to school.

School start again in January. This may be why there are few logs in January. But we do not know why there are few logs in February.

Maybe people are not so excited about the project any more. We try to make people more excited. We have a special week in March called the Carpool Challenge Week. This make more people write in the log.

One problem is to keep people doing the project. People like to drive their car. This is part of our way of life.

We give out prizes. These are gift cards to restaurants, coffee shops, and stores. We wanted to try bigger prizes. Maybe a bike, a hybrid car, or an electric car. This may make more people join.

We did not change the prizes. Maybe bigger prizes later in the project would make more people join.

An ETF is a way to have many stocks. It acts like one stock, but holds many inside. This is like a basket.  An ETF is like a fund, but it changes price like a single stock. You can buy one share of an ETF. You can also sell. This is good for investors. ETFs are cheaper than many funds. But, you pay to buy and sell them. You also pay for a fund.

ETFs have many types. It is good to look at what is inside an ETF. Is it really spread out? It is good to compare ETFs to the stocks inside.

This paper looks at ETF IHF. We look at its top ten stocks. They make up most of the ETF. We want to see if just these ten stocks are as good as the whole ETF. We want to know if they give good returns, and if they are not too risky. 

We look at the returns and risk of the ETF and the ten stocks. The ten stocks had better returns than the ETF. They were also less risky. This means picking just these ten stocks could be better. 

But, we need to know for sure. We look at the risk of each stock. Then we compare it to the risk of the ETF.

Dream-Land is one of Edgar Allan Poe’s good poems. Poe uses the word “Thule” in his poem.  The word comes from the writer Virgil. Virgil wrote about an island called Thule.  It is north of Britain. Greeks thought this island was the edge of the world. Virgil use the word Thule. Poe liked to read German writers.  One writer was Goethe. A writer named Karl J. Arndt said Poe copied Goethe. 

Oxford English Literature says Goethe was a famous writer. He wrote a play called Faust.  It was published in two parts. The first part came out in 1808. The second part came out in 1832, the year Goethe died.

Faust has a short poem called “The King of Thule.”  The poem is about a king. His wife dies. She gives him a cup. After she dies, the king drinks a lot. He is sad. He remembers his wife. He wants to die. He gives his things to his children. He keeps the cup. He walks to a cliff. He throws the cup in the sea. He closes his eyes. He dies. The king in “Dream-Land” is like the king in “The King of Thule.” Maybe Poe was sad about something and drank too much.  

Poe uses the word “Thule” two times in his writing. He uses it in “The Pit and the Pendulum” and in “Dream-Land.” “The King of Thule” and “Dream-Land” are like friends. In “Dream-Land,” the speaker talks about Thule. It is dark and lonely.  The speaker sees dead friends. He sees a world without color.  The king in “The King of Thule” is sad. He is lonely. He does not want to rule. He does not want to live.

Goethe was important. Poe would have known him. Poe liked Tennyson. Poe said he liked Tennyson. Poe read a lot of German writing.  He read Goethe.

A person fell in a store. The store had a spill. The person hurt them self. Can the person get extra money from the store?

A judge will not say no to this case. To get extra money, the person must show the store worker knew the spill was bad. They must also show the worker did not care. 

The person, Jennifer, will say the manager knew spills were bad. Other people had fallen before. He did not clean the spill. Jennifer will say the manager did not care about people. He did not clean the spill.


Jennifer fell on October 13, 2009. At 5:00 pm, an worker said there was a spill. The manager said he was eating.  At 5:15 pm, another worker said the spill was still there. The manager said the same thing. At 5:30 pm, Jennifer fell. She hurt her back.

Before this, five other people fell in the store. Jennifer wants money for her hurt.

In California, a person can get extra money if the store was very bad. This can be because the store lied, was mean, or did not care. 

The judge will look at if the manager knew the spill was bad. The judge will look at if the manager did not care.

Four years ago I went to a class about Islam. We talked a lot about if Islam was a bad religion. This is still a big question. After 9/11, the news talked a lot about Islam in a bad way. Now, they talk about it in a good way. In 2001, a president could not be Muslim. Now, we have Barack Obama.

I read about Muhammad's life. It is interesting. I thought Muhammad was mean. He took over groups and made them be Muslim. But his life story says he was kind. People came to him because he was good.

Some things about Muhammad are like Jesus. He made food for a lot of people.  The story makes Muhammad look good. It is like they are copying Jesus.

There are a lot of stories about people joining Islam. But the stories come from other people. I think this makes the stories not as good.

I do not like that they make Muhammad look good. History says he was not good. Maybe Muslims do not know the real story about Muhammad.

Jesus teach good idea. People change these idea when Jesus no more.  People look at history. Christianity change a lot.  

Today, world change fast.  Some people like old ways.  They no like new ways.  But old people no have big power.

Christians learn more about history.  They want to know what Jesus really teach.  This take long time.  Maybe many years.  But Christianity go back to old ways.  

People take away bad idea from Christianity.  Christianity go back to Jesus.  This like clock go back.  When this happen, church strong.  But all people think same.  All people do same.

This happen before.  People hurt Jesus followers.  But later, Roman people follow Jesus.  Black people no have power. Now, black people have power.

Same thing happen to Christianity.  Christianity go back to old ways.  People read Jesus words in new way.  

Before Jesus, people follow Judaism.  Judaism make Christianity.  People in that time follow one God.  They read old books. 

Judaism have many groups.  Sadducees, Pharisees, Essenes, Zealots, and common people.

The book *The Jungle* shows that people are bad. They only care about themself. They want good things, but not for others. *The Jungle* shows this with the factory owners. They make big factories. They do not care if people get hurt. Upton Sinclair writes, "The line of the buildings stood clear-cut and black against the sky; here and there out of the mass rose the great chimneys, with the river of smoke streaming away to the end of the world."  This shows how much pollution the factories make. The owners do not care about people or animals. They do not care about the smoke or the waste.

The owners also do not care about their workers. They want to make more money. They make workers do bad jobs. They fire workers without warning. The workers have no help. The workers are treated bad. The book says they are like slaves. Sinclair writes, "Here is a population, low-class and mostly foreign, hanging always on the verge of starvation and dependent for its opportunities of life upon the whim of men every bit as brutal and unscrupulous as the old-time slave drivers; under such circumstances, immorality is exactly as inevitable, and as prevalent, as it is under the system of chattel slavery."

Many writers use ways to give readers a feeling about important things. Some ways work better than others. F. Scott Fitzgerald uses many ways in his book *The Great Gatsby*. Sometimes, he uses words that do not usually go together to make a feeling. Other times, he uses things to stand for ideas and feelings. Fitzgerald does this with colors like gold, green, white, gray, and red. In *The Great Gatsby*, he gives special meanings to white/gray and red/pink. Then he uses these meanings to make readers feel something about important things in the story.

Fitzgerald uses white/gray to mean the same. White is a bit nicer, more fancy. Gray is older and faded. He shows this at the start of the story. Daisy and Jordan wear white all the time. Nick wears white to Gatsby's party. Tom wears white when he meets Myrtle. Catherine is very pale white. The only time people are not in white is when Nick is at Gatsby's party. There are many bright colors there. Fitzgerald also uses white/gray for normal things. Nick goes to work in "white" places. Names at Gatsby's party are "gray". Catherine's apartment looks like a big white cake. He also calls people and places white or gray if they are plain. 

After Fitzgerald gives white/gray these meanings, he uses them to show that things are not important. He does this with Daisy. After a long time without using white/gray, he describes Daisy in white. Readers start to see Daisy as less of a person and more like something Gatsby wants. 

Fitzgerald uses more of this with Daisy to make her seem like she is just part of a pattern. Her fur collar is a "gray haze". She wears white before Tom and Gatsby fight.

San Diego County is good for farming. The weather is warm and sunny. Farmers grow many things there, like tomatoes, oranges, lettuce, squash, broccoli, herbs, peaches, lemons, berries, honey, and peppers. People in San Diego like to buy food from nearby farms. Many farms sell food without chemicals.

People like to buy eggs and milk from these farms, too. Some farms let people visit and see how they grow food. They also let people walk and watch birds. This is good for the farm because it can make money and teach people about farming.


Farming without chemicals is good for plants and animals. There are more different kinds of plants and animals. But it can cost more money to farm this way. Farmers have to work harder to keep bugs and weeds away. They also have to use more time and money to make the soil good. Farms without chemicals are smaller and cannot grow as much.

There are other things farmers can do to help animals, even if they do not farm without chemicals. They can plant special plants to help animals. They can move cows around to different areas. They can get rid of bad plants. They can also grow plants in ways that help animals. All of these things cost more money. 

The farm is near a town called Potrero. It is 160 acres of land with trees and plants. It is next to a big forest. There are many plants and animals that live there. Some are in danger of disappearing. This land was used by Native Americans a long time ago. Then, people used it to raise cows and cut wood. Now someone wants to use it to grow food.

Culture help make talk good. Culture is many things. It is not same for every one. It is not one thing. We can not say all people in one country are the same. For example, we can not say all people from Japan are nice. This is not true.

To talk well with people from another place, we must understand their culture. We must see how their ideas are different.

When we talk to people from another place, we see things in a way we know. We like to compare. But we must be careful. We do not want to judge. We must be open to learn.

Culture is not only about country. Companies have their own culture too. Some companies work long hours. Some companies work less. We can see culture in how people dress, how they talk, and how they hire people. Some companies want people to help others.

Culture is important. It tells us why people do things. If people value face, they will not say bad things about people they work with. If people value hard work, they will not stop talking until they get a good deal. We must learn about culture before we talk to people. But we must also learn about the people we talk to.

The Bible say, "The fool say in his heart, 'There is no God.'" This is in Psalm 14. Saint Anselm use this for his ideas about God. Saint Thomas Aquinas also believe this. Both men want to show that God is real. We will look at both men's ideas. We will say that both men are right about God.

Anselm say we can know God by looking inside our mind. He say God is in our thoughts. We can not think of God not being. So God must be real. Anselm say we do not need proof from the world to know God. We know God in our mind. This is called faith.

Aquinas say we can know God by looking at the world. He say we can see God's power in things like change and how things work. He say God is like a puzzle piece. We can see the rest of the puzzle, so we know the missing piece is there. Aquinas say we can know God without faith.

Both men have good ideas about God. But neither man show us all we need to know.

Buddha was a prince. He was born long ago, maybe in the fifth or sixth century BCE. He left the world and became wise. His teaching made Buddhism. Buddhism is old. It is about two thousand five hundred years old. 

Buddhism is different now than when Buddha lived. This can be seen in Sri Lanka. There, monks and people do a water-cutting ceremony each year. Buddha did not talk about this ceremony. 

Buddhism has changed over time. It has changed on the inside and the outside. Some changes are small. Some changes are big.

This paper will use some words. 

* Internal means from inside Buddhism. It can be from monks or from people who are not monks.

* External means from people who are not Buddhist.

* Hostile means bad. It hurts Buddhism.

* Benign means not bad. It does not hurt or help Buddhism.

First, we will talk about the ideas of Buddhism. Buddhists believe in the Buddha, the Dhamma, and the Sangha. The Dhamma is the teaching of Buddhism.

The Dhamma has three parts:

* The Sutta Pitaka has the Buddha's talks.
* The Vinaya Pitaka has rules for monks.
* The Abhidhamma Pitaka has deep ideas about Buddhism.

Buddhism says that life has suffering. This is called Dukkha.  Buddhism says that we want too much. This causes suffering. Buddhism says that we can end suffering. Buddhist say that we can end the cycle of life and death. This is called Sansara. We can end Sansara if we end our wanting, our anger, and our confusion.

The United States and Mexico had a big fight for many years. It went for 57 years, from 1836 to 1893. The big fight was called the Mexican-American War. The war was from 1846 to 1848. The United States won the war. The United States took Texas and the American Southwest. 

The two countries fought many times after that. The fights stopped before World War One.

The fight started because the United States and Mexico had different ideas about religion, culture, and how to live. They also wanted the same things. This is like other countries that fight. Countries next to each other often have fights because they want the same things.

The United States had big problems with Mexico and Cuba. David M. Pletcher said that.

The United States and Mexico did not like each other because of religion. A long time ago, the United States did not like Catholicism and kings. This is like the Cold War. The United States and the Soviet Union did not like each other because they had different ideas.

The United States and Mexico did not trust each other because of their history. Their old rulers did not like each other.

The two countries had many fights. Most fights were about land. Bandits from the United States would go into Mexico and steal things. The United States and Mexico sent soldiers to stop this.

The United States and Mexico finally stopped fighting. Mexico needed the United States. The United States wanted to help Mexico's economy.

Fifteen years ago, I got sick. I could not work. I was a nurse. At that time, I was forty-six years old and single. I did not have much money.  I live on help from the government now. I have nothing else. Every day is hard. I am afraid. I do not know what will happen.

I need help from my family and friends. They help me.

Bad things happen to people. We need to help each other.

In the United States, some people say we need to help ourselves.  We need to be strong. But in the past, people helped each other. They shared food and worked together.

It is good to be ready for bad things. I have supplies. I have food and water. I have a plan.

But it is also good to know your neighbors.

Why do living things change over time? Are there limits to how they change? 

A long time ago, a scientist said that we still do not know how to use math to explain how living things are made. This is still true today. 

Scientists are now using math to study how seashells grow. They are also using math to study how seashells change over many years.

This study looks at seashells called Prunum. Using pictures of Prunum shells, scientists found ways to measure how the shells change shape. They used a computer program to make new shell shapes.

These new shapes can help us understand how seashells change over time.

A seashell is like a tube that spins around. Each spin is called a whorl. The whorls are all around a center line called the columella. The size of the whorls can change. A line between each whorl is called a suture.

The last whorl is the biggest. All the whorls except the last one make the spire. The top of the spire is the apex. The other end is the base.

The animal lives inside the shell. It comes out through an opening called the aperture.

We can look at shells in different ways. The most common way is to look at the aperture.

We can count the whorls by looking at the shell from the top. Then we draw a line to divide the shell in half. We count the whorls from that line.

A shell grows over time. We can track the growth by looking at the center of each whorl. We can also look at the size of each opening.

This information can be used to make a graph and a math equation. This can help us understand how seashells grow.

Indonesia has a problem with baby and new mother deaths.  The number of deaths has stayed the same for ten years.  Indonesia is good at some things, like giving clean water to people. But Indonesia needs to help more mothers and babies.

Indonesia is better at helping mothers have babies with a doctor. Many babies now have a doctor at birth. But some doctors are not real doctors, like midwives.  They cannot help if a baby is sick.  So, Indonesia still needs to work on this problem.

Indonesia is also bad at helping babies who are sick with diarrhea.  It is hard to get help for babies after they are born.

Indonesia does not do many cesarean sections. This is bad because cesarean sections can save lives.  

Indonesia has more doctors in cities.  Poor people have a hard time getting to doctors.  This is a big problem.

Indonesia needs to decide how to help more mothers and babies.  

Some people think Indonesia should have special programs.  These programs work fast, but they are not always good.

Special programs can take money from other parts of the health system.  They can also make work harder for doctors.

Victorian novels are known for close looks at small details and stories about rich people. Two books,  *Oliver Twist* and *Wuthering Heights*, are from this time but do not follow this pattern. Both books have mystery and strange parts, which is not common for books from this time. This helps the reader understand the characters better and why they act the way they do.


Here is a part from *Oliver Twist*:

“Many strange thoughts came into his mind. He felt like he was still with Sikes and Crackit, who were arguing. He could hear their words. Then he saw he was talking to them….  Suddenly, he heard gunshots. People cried out. Lights flashed. Everything was loud and confusing. An unseen hand took him away quickly. Through all of this, he felt a bad pain that would not go away.


The two books use mystery often in dreams or dreamlike scenes. But the meaning and purpose are different in each scene. In *Oliver Twist*, these strange events show us about Oliver’s feelings and what hurts him.  He knows things are not always what they seem. When Oliver is shot in chapter 28, he remembers it clearly, like a dream, while he is trying to find help.  The writing shows that Oliver had no control over what happened. He was very sick. He saw Sikes and Crackit, which shows how much pain he was in. The shooting was so bad that he did not notice the hand that carried him away. He felt pain all the time, not just the pain from the shot.

The question is, who was responsible for Oliver's bad luck? It was not his fault.  This shows that Oliver had no control over his life. He could not control what happened, even when he was in danger. We see that Oliver felt defeated. He was starting to accept his bad luck, because Fagin had hurt him so much that he could not fight back.

Here is a part from *Wuthering Heights*:

“The day went by quickly – day! There was no day; it was gone as soon as it came – and night came again; night so long, and yet so short; long in its silence and short in its passing hours.”

A few years ago, I work in a school program. I help young students. I was good at English and reading. A teacher ask me to help a boy named Adrian. He was in third or fourth grade. He have hard time reading.

I think something was wrong. He read some letters good. He read other letters bad. It was strange. Adrian spoke good English. We try to help him, but it was hard. Then, I meet Adrian's mother. I was watching other children when his mother came. She only speak Spanish. I did not speak much Spanish. But we talk a little.

Then I understand. Adrian could read. He did not know the English letters well. I do not know if this help him much, but I hope he is doing better now.

I tell this story to talk about language problems in schools. It is a big problem in California. It is not always easy to see. A child can speak English well, but reading can be hard. We all know this is a problem. What can we do?

For Adrian, the answer was simple. I help him learn English letters and sounds. But for children who do not speak much English, the answer is harder. There is no one way to fix this. We need to try many things.

Dual language programs are a good idea. They help all children. Some people are afraid of these programs. They think they waste money. But this is not true. If we use these programs more, all children will learn more.

How can we do this? We do not need all teachers to speak two languages. This is too hard. But we can have special helpers who speak two languages.

From the time we are little, many people say there is some thing big, bigger than us. We can not know it. Some people go to church. Some go to temple. Some look inside themself. Many people take the beliefs of their parents. Some people say, "No! There is no thing beyond us!" They say only their own world is real. We like some things now. We like other things later. We try to know who we are. We look for light in the dark.

My father said, "A cardinal," when I asked what bird he liked best. We sat on our porch. Rain fell hard on the roof. We smoked. Rain made the plants wet. My father looked at the rain. He looked sad. He was thinner. His hair was short. He did not look at me. I felt alone. I was afraid. I could not talk to him about missing him. It would make it real. I held him. I moved my chair closer. We looked at the rain.

My father died in December. He was five days past my birthday. He had sickness. He was not strong. I did not know if the sickness helped him. I thought, "What kind of God does this?" I did not pray. I thought if God was real, he did not listen.

I did not want to see him die. I did not want to watch. I wanted to remember him as he lived. I knew him better than anyone. I knew he did not want me there. I stayed in bed for three days.

No one called me.

The "Gothic Novel" is old and new. This is what Ian Watt says in his book "The Rise of the Gothic Novel". Some people say the Gothic style is not good. Others say it is very good. It can make people feel scared and happy at the same time. The first Gothic Novel was "The Castle of Otranto" by Horace Walpole. It used old stories and new ideas to make a new kind of story. Walpole used old theater and new ways to write about nature. He called it "A Gothic Story".

Gothic stories use old ideas from the Middle Ages. They use old buildings, stories, and ways of life. Even when "The Castle of Otranto" was first published, the word "Gothic" was used for many things. People thought it was old-fashioned. They thought new things were better.

Gothic stories are old and new at the same time. They use old ideas but in a new way. This is why they are still popular today.

One old idea in Gothic stories is chivalry. Chivalry is the way knights were trained. It was important to Gothic writers because it showed what a good knight should be like: brave, honest, and strong. Gothic writers thought that people today were not like that.

Walpole wrote "The Castle of Otranto" during a time of trouble. He was worried about the future. Maybe he thought that people in the past were better than people today. In his story, we see this in the character Frederic. He is a prince. He has been sad and lost his family. He is supposed to be dead.

The story describes Frederic as a good knight. He is brave and kind. This shows how Gothic writers thought about the past. They saw it as a time of honor and courage.

Supply chain management is the way goods go from a customer order to the customer. It starts with raw materials. Then, goods are made, sent out, and finally reach the customer. The term “supply chain management” was used for the first time in 1982. A man named Keith Oliver came up with it. He said it is the way to plan, do, and check the whole process. This is done to make sure customers are happy and get what they want quickly.

There are six parts to a supply chain: making things, getting materials, keeping things in stock, choosing good places, moving things, and sharing information. Business leaders use these parts to make their customers happy.

Making things is the first part. It is the base of the whole process.  

Managers make plans for when, where, and how things will be made. They need to know what customers want. A good way to know is to look at the market. The market shows what customers want. 

After looking at the market, managers decide what to make and how much. Then, they decide where to make things. They need to pick a place that can make things well and quickly. The best place also makes sure customers are happy.

Once the place is picked, managers plan how much work to do each day. They also take care of the machines. Making things is very important.  Every small detail matters. If things are not planned well, it can cost a lot of time and money in the end.

For example, I used to work at Wal-Mart and Target. Both stores have plans for everything they do. They have rules about how to make things, how to take care of things, and how to get things. These plans help things run smoothly.

The second part is getting supplies. This means making good plans for where things are made and who helps make things. A company might have many different places to make things. Each place might have different workers and tools. Managers have to pick the best place for each part of the process.

Sometimes, managers ask other companies to help make things. This is called outsourcing. Managers do this to make things faster and cheaper.

Hitler alive in Burma, sign say.

Ellen Page, star of Juno, stand alone. She hold a sign. The sign have a message. It is strange. Burma, also called Myanmar, is a country. It is in Southeast Asia. A group of soldiers rule Burma. They take power in 1962. In 2007, people have protests. They want change. Monks lead the protests. People call them "The Saffron Revolution." Monks wear yellow robes. At first, soldiers let monks protest. But then, things get bad. Soldiers use force. They hurt people. Soldiers hurt monks. Some monks die.

A Japanese man, Kenji Nagai, take pictures of the protests. Soldiers arrest him. He die. Many people die, but the soldiers say only a few die.

This is not new. Leaders want power. They do not like people to speak out. This happen many times in history. Roman leaders say they are from gods. Japanese leaders say they are gods too.

In 1989, people protest in China. Soldiers hurt them. Many people die. In Rwanda, people kill each other. This is called genocide. Hitler hurt many people who are Jewish.

Duke Ellington make good music. He play piano good. He lead a band for many years. Ellington make music that is new and different. His music good for solo players. He make music that sound good together. 

Ellington’s music use voice like an instrument. He use this in a song call “Creole Love Call.” This song use voice and music to make a new sound. 

Ellington also use voice in a song call “Hot and Bothered.” He use trumpet and voice to make a new sound.  

Ellington make music that is fun to listen to. His music is very good.

She want some thing. She want this thing bad. It start when she was about 14. She was a teen. It still there now. She is 17. Now, she want a person. But she no want boy. Some boy like her. They try to talk to her, but she no want them. She ask herself why. She try to think. Why she no like boy? She think a lot. She have idea, but no good idea. She live her life. She still ask herself why.

Her home is peace. Her parent are good. They no fight. They no fight with her much. They only fight when she want to do her own thing. She have fun. She like to talk. People like her.

Today is no peace day. She walk in her house. She want to do some thing new. She hear a scream. It her mother's voice. She run to the kitchen. "Mom! What wrong?" Her mother on the ground. She say "Ow". 

Her daughter run to her mother. "Mom, what wrong?" "My sweet, I need help. I need the hospital." Her mother hurt bad. "Okay, Mom. Where I take you?" "Here," her mother say. The daughter take her mother to the car. She take care of her mother.


The hospital smell bad. But the daughter no care. She want to help her mother. She run to the doctor. The doctor come to her mother. They take her mother. The daughter wait. 

Her mother fall off a chair. She want a thing on a high shelf.

This study looked at if eating like people in the Mediterranean area helps keep your heart healthy. They looked at a group of women who ate a lot of plants, fruits, and nuts. They also ate less meat and fat. This is called the “alternate Mediterranean (aMed) diet.”

Doctors saw that these women had less heart problems and strokes. They followed these women for many years. They gave them tests to see what they ate. They also looked at their health records.

The women who ate more like people in the Mediterranean area were healthier. They had less heart attacks and strokes.

The United States had a big problem in two thousand seven. Many people lost jobs. Houses cost less money. Big companies had trouble. This problem is not over yet. We need to know how this happened. We need to know how to stop it. 

This problem was caused by people making poor choices. They made banks give out too many bad loans. The banks were not ready for this. Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac also made bad choices. They put these bad loans into packages and sold them. 

This problem started in one nine ninety nine when President Clinton was in office. He wanted to be president again. He wanted people to like him. He made it easy for banks to give out loans.

A reporter from the New York Times said this could be a problem in the future. He was right.  

Many things caused this problem. People took out loans they could not pay back. Banks gave out loans that were too risky. This made the problem worse.

The cost of houses went up too high. Then the prices went down. Banks lost a lot of money. Some big banks had to close.

Exposition is part of a story. It can be good or bad.  Good exposition shows the reader things. Bad exposition tells the reader things.

A good writer does not tell the reader everything. They show the reader. For example, a writer might say a woman is happy.  Or, they might show the woman smiling and laughing.

Exposition can be too long sometimes. This is bad. The reader gets tired.

Dr. Merlin is a teacher. She teaches writing. She sees bad exposition all the time. She says, "Show, do not tell."

Exposition can be about a character.  A writer might tell the reader a character is strong. But, a good writer shows the character lifting something heavy.

 Exposition is like a meal. Too much food is bad. Just enough food is good.

I see two news from Columbus, Ohio. The first news was NBC 4 this morning (August 13, 2011). The main story was about a man in Ashley, Ohio. He hurt his wife. They did not say her name, but his name was Shad Hostettler. They showed his picture. He looked bad. They said he hurt his wife many times. He was stopped by the police. I think they talked about this story for a good amount of time. 

The second story was about a man named Travis Buyers. He was 18 years old. He was hurt by a gun in the morning. The police are looking for the person who hurt him. There are no arrests yet. I think this story was short. I think this is because he was a black man. I have seen this before. When a white person is hurt, the news talks a lot about it. But when a black person is hurt, the news does not talk about it very much.

The next story was about a hole in a helicopter. Someone shot at the helicopter. It was a small bullet. The police want to know who did it. They will give money to anyone who knows who did it.

The next story was about the rain. It will rain on Saturday. It will be hot. The news wanted to tell you about this so you would watch.

The next story was about a robbery. A man hurt a store worker. He was black. He wore a hat. The police want to find him. I think they talked about his skin color too much.

The last story was about a man named Rene Rodriguez. He was in jail. He sold drugs. He was from Texas. He will be in jail for a long time.

Brothers have a strong link. This link has many feelings: love, pride, jealousy, and meanness. Brothers know each other very well. They see themselves in their brother. This link is strong, even when things are bad. When a brother does good or bad, the link is clear. It is important to understand these feelings. 

Brothers look at each other and see their own true self. They see how they act and what they do. This shows who they really are. The story "The Scarlet Ibis" shows this link between brothers. Two brothers go on a trip. They have strong feelings. They have pride and sadness. Only one brother lives. 

The story shows how the brother feels about his little brother, Doodle. The brother wants to teach Doodle things like how to run, jump, and climb. He wants a brother to play with. But Doodle is sick. He can't do these things. This makes the brother sad. He is angry at Doodle. He even thinks about hurting Doodle. But then Doodle smiles. The brother feels love for him.

The human brain is very hard. It works like a machine. It takes in facts and makes new ideas. 

Long ago, people said the brain was like a tablet. Then they said it was like paper. Now people say it is like a computer. But the brain is different.

Facts go into the brain through our senses. We can see, hear, touch, smell, and taste. The brain changes these facts into signals. The brain uses these signals to learn.

First, the brain looks at small parts of a fact. Then, it looks at the whole fact. For example, we see a black box on a white background. The brain sees the black color and the shape. It knows it is a box.

The brain also pays attention to important things. We can see many things, but we only think about some things.

The brain stores facts. There are many kinds of memory. Some facts stay for a short time. Other facts stay for a long time.

The brain stores facts in many ways. Some facts are stored as words. Other facts are stored as pictures.

People try to understand how the brain works. They use computers to help them.

Aldous Huxley talk about the danger of new technology. He also talk about the bad way that money works. He make a story about a bad place called Brave New World. The people in this place like to be together and happy. They do not like to think about big ideas.

The people in Brave New World are like parts of a machine. They do what the World Controller tell them to do. Huxley think that this is bad. He think that this way of life is like what Karl Marx talk about. Marx say that when people only think about making money, it hurts them.

Huxley use a word called "false consciousness." This mean that the people do not know how bad things really are. They think that they are happy, but they are not. The World Controller keep the people happy by giving them things to buy. This is how the World Controller stay in power.

The people in Brave New World do not have any real friends. They do not love each other. They are all the same. Huxley think that this is because of the technology and money. He say that they make people forget how to be human.

I go to school at University Park for two and a half years. I am in my fifth semester. Many students have trouble getting around campus. My first year, I lived in East Halls. It is far from the center of campus. Going to classes far away, like Willard building, could take twenty-five minutes by foot. It is often bad weather here.

I spoke to a former student. He said that long ago, East Halls was far from the rest of the school. There was much empty land. Now, there are sports fields, new buildings, and apartments. More buildings make it hard to get around.

What is the best way to get around campus? A bicycle is good. But students must ride them. The campus must be good for bicyclists.

I spoke to a friend. He rode a bicycle a few years ago. He said bikes are good. He said they are the only way to get around. Bicycles are good for your body. They are also the fastest way to travel.

I live off campus now. It is far from the center of campus. I bought a bicycle this year. It is good. I have class in Thomas building. It is a twenty-five-minute walk. On my bicycle, it takes five minutes.

Pollock Road is the best way to get to Thomas building. But it is not always safe to ride a bicycle there.

Walking is good. But I am too busy to walk. If I did not have a bicycle, I would have to walk. It would take me thirty to forty minutes to walk to Thomas building each day. That is two and a half hours a week. I do not have time for that.

In pursuing an education in social work, I intend to follow a career path with the Division of Family and Children Services to help children who have been abused or neglected; and to provide support for troubled families. Values that I can provide to the social work field include the following: service, respect, ethical nature, commitment to help improve relationships between others and to improve myself professionally to remain competent in my field. These core values are not just important to social workers; they are important to me personally. 

	I have always wanted to help others, but I was unsure of the career path that I wanted to follow. Throughout my years in high school and college, I saw many individuals flee from their problems in denial and a few used coping mechanisms that were less than ideal. Because of situations that I have witnessed, I chose to pursue a Bachelor’s degree in Psychology. Still unsure of a career path, I decided to take a break once I graduated from Piedmont College in 2009. One day that summer, I visited a friend who introduced me to a sixteen year-old boy sitting nervously on her couch. She explained to me why he was visiting: to escape his abusive parents. The next day, I learned that he had called the police to his parent’s residence. To see if I could help in any way, I drove over to his parents’ house. Once there, I privately explained my concerns to the police and told them I had just graduated with a degree in Psychology from Piedmont College. The police requested that I talk to the parents since there was nothing that the law could do for the teenager. When I questioned the parents about the situation, they seemed nervous and used excuses to describe their son’s “manipulative” behavior for involving outside sources to resolve “simple” disputes. After this particular experience, I began to seriously consider a career in social work to help children with “simple” disputes among family members.

	Another value that is important for the field of social work is social justice. As a society, we claim that the individual is important and we mourn those that we have lost. The concept of the “individual” that society holds is more a follower of archaic traditions than actual uniqueness. So, if society mourns lost individuals, then why do we strive to be similar to “everyone else?” I am an individual and do not enjoy placing limitations on myself to be similar to others. Throughout my years at high school and college, I protested against social injustice whenever I could: coloring my hair unnatural colors, wearing clothing that fit my personality, piercing my ears past the traditional set, declaring my involvement with GSBA (Gay Straight Bisexual Alliance), fighting against both racism and discrimination whenever I witnessed it, etc. I believe in social justice and I will continue to protest against social injustice.

The following paper addresses the Biological and Sociocultural models in relation to the disorder insomnia. The biological model focuses on genetic information that is inherited as well as medical aspects of health. The Sociocultural models look at environmental relationships and their applications to race, ethnicity, demographics, and socioeconomic status. The following review of insomnia looks at these models and explains each piece of research chosen to relate to and to better explain the models. The explanations of the research and their findings are then critiqued to mention their specific strengths and weaknesses.

A sleep disorder can be characterized as a primary sleep disorder, a sleep disorder related to another mental disorder, or a sleep disorder related to other issues. The Primary sleep disorders are Dyssonmias or Parasomnias while sleep disorders related to another mental disorder are related to an Axis I or Axis II disorder. Other categories of sleep disorders can be due to medical complications or the intake of a substance. The Dyssomnias are: Primary Insomnia, Primary Hypersomnia, Narcolepsy, Breathing- Related Sleep Disorder, Circadian Rhythm Sleep Disorder, and Dyssomnia Not Otherwise Specified (NOS). While Primary Insomnia is a complication in adequate or maintained sleep, Primary Hypersomnia is a difficulty in staying awake, both for at least a one month period of time. Narcolepsy involves cataplexy and/ or automatic REM. While Dyssonmias focus on initiating and remaining asleep, the Parasomnias are sleep disorders associated with behavioral abnormalities and/ or physiological occurrences. Parasomnias are Nightmare Disorder, Sleep Terror Disorder, Sleepwalking Disorder, and Parasomnias Not Otherwise Specified. The sleep disorders related to another mental disorder involve sleep difficulties due to Axis I (Clinical Disorders) or Axis II (Personality Disorders or Mental Retardation). The following review focuses on insomnia, and somewhat on primary sleep disorders in general in relation to the biological and sociocultural models.

	 The biological model of sleep disorders focuses on genes, heritable factors, and physiologically acquired aspect of sleep disorders. Neurons in the hypothalamus containing orexin are responsible for the regulation of sleep and wakefulness. This study experimented with mice and found that there are phenotypic GABAB receptors on the orexin neurons which are specifically responsible for sleep/ wake states. The activation of the GABAA receptor induces responses that promote sleep. If it is inhibited from firing, this can cause reduced anxiety and induce sleep. The GABAB agonist (baclofen) increased sleep time (Matsuki et al., 2009). Such results imply that the animal models of mice can be generalized to studies in humans. This shows that there is a genetic and environmental basis for the physical GABAB receptor in humans. A problem or absence with this receptor could alter the ability of one to have adequate sleep without medication. The sociocultural implication of this study is that if the phenotype was inherited, this could regulate sleep, and an alteration of the receptor would naturally disturb sleep for an individual. This would negatively impact aspects of life such as school, career, and every day events that involve monotonous tasks and focus.

This paper covers three areas of Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD). First, a brief definition of the disorder is provided. Next, diagnosis is explained, with common characteristics, or “red flags”. Finally, the paper concludes with ways that a teacher in a mainstreamed classroom environment can assist a student with CAPD.

	Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD), or Auditory Processing Disorder (APD) “refers to the efficiency and effectiveness by which the central nervous system (CNS) utilizes auditory information. Narrowly defined, (C)AP refers to the perceptual processing of auditory information in the CNS and the neurobiologic activity that underlies that processing and gives rise to electrophysiologic auditory potentials” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005), meaning it is a disorder wherein the central nervous system (i.e. the brain) cannot properly process things that are heard. People with CAPD can hear normally, and are therefore not considered “hearing impaired”; rather, the area of the brain that translates what we hear, separating words or differentiating conversation from background noise does not function as it typically should. 

	The earliest mention of the disorder that became CAPD is from the mid-1950s, called “auditory imperception” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005) when researchers were evaluating children with communicative disorders. The Italian research team of Bocca, Calearo, and Cassinari began developing tests for these children in 1954; in 1961, Kimura “introduced dichotic testing and formulated a model to explain the physiology of the CANS underlying dichotic perception” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005). A national conference was held in 1977 that stimulated research on children with CAPD. 

	CAPD manifests itself in multiple ways: the person suffering may not be able to localize or hear sound in space; may have difficulty discriminating between two or more “acoustic events” (sound occurrences); may not be able to recognize sound patterns; may not be able to differentiate changes in speech (like detecting sarcasm based on change of voice); one sound may be blocked by a subsequent sound; may not have the ability to synthesize sound clues (that is, interpret in a meaningful way that they can then act upon); and may not be able to determine the sequence in which auditory information is presented (Ferre).

	In order to diagnose CAPD, the patient must be screened with “systematic observation of listening behavior and/or performance on tests of auditory function”, which may be conducted by “audiologists, SLPs, psychologists, and others using a variety of measures that evaluate auditory-related skills” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005). This may include questionnaires and surveys, observation of auditory behaviors, including how the patient responds to certain stimuli. There is, at this time, no one tool or test that is used consistently to a high rate of diagnostic success, and there is no known cause for the disorder. Many tests used present the patient with multiple, simultaneous auditory stimuli and then ask for them to differentiate certain items, like a series of words or numbers. More advanced tests include recording acoustic signals within the ear and measuring the responses to the signals.

The play Twelfth Night seems to say that although disguise is in fact useful in perpetrating long bouts of deception, in the end a person must reject that newly formed guise, or else risk losing themselves forever in the process. A big problem with ending a deception, however, is that one may find themselves alienated in the process. Therefore, in the end, one must decide between one’s own self preservation, or the preservation of relationships with those around them. For although some will respond neutrally to discovering that they’ve been tricked, still others will not take the deception so lightly, and will be likely be offended by the whole charade.
The topic of deception in gender role reversal is especially problematic, because it brings up many side issues, perhaps the most important one being, why? Why does the subject feel the need to shirk their own identity and take up a disguise in the form of the opposite gender? In Viola’s case, it is obviously a form of self protection.: “I’ll bring you to a captain in this town/ Where lie my maiden weeds, by whose gentle help/ I was preserved to serve this noble count…” (5.1.247-249)
Having newly arrived in a foreign land, Viola feels it necessary to pretend to be a man to protect herself from would be attackers. Viola’s plan works, but it also alienates her from the women around her, cutting her off from an important support system. To make matters worse, she is apparently so convincing at appearing to be a man that Olivia confuses her with Sebastian, and in effect falls in love with her. “Whither, my lord? Cesario, husband, stay.” (5.1.138) On top of that, she also has to deal with suppressed romantic desires between her and Orsino: “Boy, thou hast said to me a thousand times/ Thou never shouldst love woman like to me.” (5.1. 260-261)
Although this may be a somewhat progressive attitude, to the modern reader, Twelfth Night may be seen as an illustration of how deception may help facilitate the unveiling of suppressed emotions, especially in the cases of Olivia and Orsino. Certain passages seem to hint that the aforesaid characters may have unexpressed subconscious desires that the appearance of Viola/Cesario forces them to deal with. For instance, is Olivia attracted to Cesario because Cesario appears to be a man, or does Olivia really secretly harbor feelings for women? One would argue that this is probably not the case, because Shakespeare’s character Olivia seems more likely to be parodying those people of his time period who judge others only upon their looks. 
This is evidenced by the ease with which Olivia switches her romantic ardors from Cesario to Sebastian, and begins to regard Cesario/Viola as family rather than a love interest: “A sister, you are she.” (5.1.315)

German colonial rule has been noted by various observers for its brutality, notably with respect to the genocide of the Ovaherero and Nama in German South West Africa. Of course nothing so broad as an entire colonial empire can be accounted for by such a simple description. The German colonial empire was as varied in policies and ruling style as it was in geography. Educational provision across the colonies was similarly diverse. When the British took over German East Africa (Tanganyika) in 1919, they found a large population of educated and literate Africans. German educational efforts in Kamerun and other colonies were also praised by contemporary authors. 
The situation in South West Africa (present-day Namibia) presented a stark contrast.  Unlike in East Africa, where the government established state schools and played a prominent role in the education of the natives, in South West Africa the task of native education was left almost entirely to missionary societies that received limited government support. The government did however invest significant resources towards the education of Europeans in the colony, establishing s system of state schools as well as more heavily supporting and regulating missionary schools. These educational policies had longstanding effects on South West Africa, even after German rule. While other German colonies boasted significant numbers of literate and educated Africans, in South West Africa “the overwhelming majority of the population remained untouched, uneducated, and illiterate.” Various social, political, and economic factors led to the divergent experience of South West Africa. This paper seeks to expand the discussion by identifying these factors and paying particular attention to new research on the attitudes of settlers and colonial authorities to native Africans.
There is a wealth of literature dealing with education in the German colonial empire specifically. Most of these sources are in German and were written in the early twentieth century, during or shortly after the period of German colonial rule. The aim of early works was primarily to describe the features of educational systems in these colonies. Later writings in English expanded the discourse through comparative studies of education in the various German colonies and more detailed analyses of specific aspects of education. These studies illustrated significant differences in the educational systems of different colonies. The most prominent work to explicitly address the topic of this paper is Cohen’s study of education in South West Africa and East Africa. Cohen compares the educational systems of the two colonies and discusses the factors that account for the differences between them. According to Cohen, the large settler population of South West Africa explains many of the distinguishing aspects of the colony’s educational system.
Compared to Germany’s other colonial possessions, South West Africa had a moderately temperate climate, although much of the territory is covered by arid desert. The European population of South West Africa reflected the relatively hospitable conditions. By 1913 nearly 15,000 whites lived in South West Africa, while only 5,336 lived in the colony with the next largest settler population, East Africa.

‎	‏The classification of Popular Music has grown over the past‭ ‬100‭ ‬years to include so many genres that it is difficult to definitively list them all. Complicating matters,‭ ‬most if not all genres—rap,‭ ‬rock,‭ ‬country,‭ ‬jazz,‭ ‬folk,‭ ‬just to name a few—have spawned multiple sub and sub-sub genres within their domain.  Arguably the sub-genre of Heavy Metal rock has become one of the most diverse and expressive genres of all popular music in the past‭ ‬40‭ ‬years. It is expressive because it displays a wide range of emotions,‭ ‬although they tend to lean toward the darker side of the spectrum. It is diverse in that quite soon after the beginnings of the genre,‭ ‬people started to realize that it had real flexibility and started to take advantage of it to create their own sub-genre,‭ ‬which then was followed by sub-sub-genres,‭ ‬and the chain continues until today. 

Today we have reached a point in the heavy metal movement where there are so many niches of groups that it is hard to determine what exactly heavy metal is. It has grown to incorporate so many themes from other genres,‭ ‬but like everything else,‭ ‬it spawned from somewhere. In order to properly understand the metal music that exists everywhere today,‭ ‬one must first understand what the metal movement is,‭ ‬and why it’s a movement rather than just a genre.

‎	‏Metal is,‭ ‬in many ways,‭ ‬a movement defined by darkness. Metal can be considered a‭ “‬music of more‭”—‬more bass,‭ ‬more volume,‭ ‬more violence,‭ ‬more theatricality. Less primitivism,‭ ‬more chops‭; ‬people in metal bands really know how to play their instrument,‭ ‬and it comes through in the music. Metal is also—although it may not come as a surprise—a movement that is heavily drug induced. There was a psychedelic drug boom in the mid-70‭’‬s that led to people getting crazier,‭ ‬leading to them to make crazy,‭ ‬other-worldly records,‭ ‬using the drugs as a scapegoat for their creation. It possesses many dark,‭ ‬visceral qualities,‭ ‬which was very new to the music scene because a large amount of popular music had qualities that weren’t true to the darker side of the emotional spectrum. Also,‭ ‬later generations of metal have taken some of their influence from the dark,‭ ‬visceral qualities that were so present in the Romantic Era. Lyrics such as the following express the darkness that is such a staple of the movement:‭ (‬Byrne‭)‬


	
These lyrics from Helter Skelter display the darker side of the Beatles. It exhibits an up and down,‭ ‬supposedly that of drugs. This song is considered by some to be one of the first Heavy Metal songs. It was a response to a Rolling Stones song that was also on the heavier,‭ ‬darker side. The Beatles wanted to prove that they could be just as heavy as the Stones,‭ ‬so they put that song on‭ ‬The White Album.

A few decades before the Surrealist artists began painting their dreamlike works, the artist Henri Rousseau was carefully crafting his own dreams, literally and figuratively. The Dream, a 1910 painting by the famous Post-Impressionist artist, represents not only a woman in awe at the wonders of the land she visits within a dream, but also Rousseau’s own personal dreams and goals as a painter. Since beginning his work, he dreamed of recognition, acceptance, and praise by other artists and art lovers, and found that he was faced with a difficult internal dilemma to achieve this aspiration. The Dream is Henri Rousseau’s work that best reflects his career-long internal struggle: to either conform to or mimic certain styles of painting in order to be accepted by the critical art world he so adored, or to allow himself to be creatively independent and unique, leaving his own path as he went.
Before one can analyze The Dream through this perspective, one must first be somewhat familiar with Rousseau’s biographical story. Henri Rousseau was born on May 21, 1844, in the town of Laval in northwest France. His father was a tinsmith and hardware dealer who “enjoyed bourgeois prosperity” (Shattuck 47). Growing up, he received no formal training in the arts; instead, he was employed until the age of forty working for France as a gabelou, or employee of the municipal toll service, although he received the misnomer sobriquet of douanier, a customs inspector (Shattuck 46). The death of his first wife, Clémence, which followed the deaths of eight infant children, left Rousseau with only one child, a daughter named Julia, and immense grief (Shattuck 49). He therefore hoped to take refuge in a new life and pursued painting to offer him comfort and fresh beginnings. Unlike contemporary colleagues of Rousseau who sentimentalize and romanticize the peasant in painting, he is essentially a folk painter and has the hopes and dreams of the average member of his class.
Rousseau’s obsession with being accepted by the art world is somewhat understandable when evaluated in context: as discussed, he was not only uneducated in the ways of formal painting and began his career at a much older age, but he was producing works at the same time as many other talented and better-known modern artists. Though working for many years already, Rousseau did not begin to receive proper recognition for his art until around the same time that Matisse had begun crafting a reputation as an artist. In the book Modern French Painters, author Jan Gordon asserts that the two, while technically competitors in the art arena, were different not only in style and subject matter but also their reasons for painting in the first place: “Matisse was a painter who conceived a terror of painting in a trite way, while Rousseau’s desire was to paint a picture so conventional that he would be admitted to the Artiste Français” (92).

Many a great thinker has postulated an intimate connection between ethics and aesthetics, between truth and beauty. I believe that at a fundamental level there is a reason for this. As John Keats says in “Ode on a Grecian Urn”, “Beauty is truth, truth beauty- That is all / Ye know on earth, and all ye need to know.” Much of what we know in life is learned via education or experience. However, we seem to appreciate ethics and aesthetics, as Keats implies, without being taught in these expected ways. Both ethics and aesthetics are an attempt to describe rather then prescribe. Our studies of morality and beauty are, for the most part, attempts to explain why a piece of art or literature is beautiful, or why an action is moral, rather than a set of rules for judging, or creating, good art or moral behavior. 
	More to the point, criticism of art or morals is never able to fully capture the essence of what is good or what is beautiful. A conversation about the worth of da Vinci's Mona Lisa, for example, may center around concepts like foreground, background, contrast, or cultural context, but in the end, these do not describe why it is good art. Rather, when one is asked about a favorite work of art or literature it is common to hear a phrase similar to, “There's just something about it” preceding a more complex or critical explanation. I believe that both art and morals can never be completely reduced to a description of their qualities. As Flannery O'Connor says, “A story is a way to say something that can't be said any other way . . . you tell a story because a statement would be inadequate.” No matter how completely we describe the properties of a work of literature, there is something transcendent which is still left. I believe that ethics has this same property. As Wittgenstein says, “It is clear that ethics cannot be expressed. / Ethics is transcendental. / . I suggest that it is this “something”, this je ne sais quoi, which is art and morality's most powerful attribute, and that this transcendental nature of both ethics and aesthetics provides a connection point between them.
	I believe that morality and art are so closely related because we experience both of them most powerfully at a noumenally, to use a Kantian term. They impact us at a level that can be experienced, but not fully explained. This link is even stronger when it comes to the art of literature. As McKean says, “What most distinguishes literature from the other arts, what is, in truth, unique about the art, is its moral quality. It may be that moral standards are inappropriate to other arts, music, for instance, but they seem to be as relevant to literature as they are to life itself. Living necessarily involves values. . . . Literature is important to us precisely because of the values we find there” .

The Germany of today is considered a strong force, a united country with its own blend of culture from within the shadows of the alps in München, all the way to Baltic sea city of Kiel.  The same culture can be felt from Köln on the river Rhine, through the centre of Germany to the Saxon city of Dresden located on the Elbe. With such a unique culture, it shouldn't be surprising that Germany as we now know it comes from several different sources, and tribes. 

Germania is the ancestral land of the Germans. The origins of the name are highly disputed among scholars and historians.
